theorem closure_interior_closure_interior_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (interior (closure (interior A))) = closure (interior A) := by
  apply subset_antisymm
  ·
    -- `interior (closure (interior A))` is contained in `closure (interior A)`,
    -- hence the same is true after taking closures.
    have h : interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
      interior_subset
    exact closure_mono h
  ·
    -- By monotonicity of `interior`, `interior A` is contained in
    -- `interior (closure (interior A))`; taking closures yields the reverse inclusion.
    have h : interior A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A)) :=
      interior_subset_interior_closure_interior (X := X) (A := A)
    exact closure_mono h
